  "text": "This section focuses on DAMDP with a finite number of decision stages. We show that a strategy defined through backward induction, which we call S-robust strategy, is distributionally robust. We further show such a strategy is solvable in polynomial time under mild technical conditions. This generalizes results in [CITATION_1] to a significantly more general class of ambiguity sets.",
